			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Yes. That is true. But in some cases mages dont get pets. I am a 7 Wizard. I prefer my cracked staff becuase I cant find anything better at the moment. I have to fight melee becuase as far as I have seen I dont get a pet. If I do then what spell would that be and what level would I get it at? So far my bashing with 1 handed blunt is doing nearly as much as my nukes. I cant hit for much either way until I gain another bubble of exp and get level 8. Once that is done I can get some of the slightly stronger spells. Also. Since I have no pet I cant stand back and nuke. The closest I can do is Root and hope that the thing doesnt resist or break free. Once it does I have no way of running becuase I only have about 120 hp with my sheild up. That gets taken down really quick becuase I seem to get hit for 26 every other swing. <br>  <br> It is also not very helpful that for some reason my character has to walk after loosing 2 bubbles of HP. Where every other character I have seen can still run as long as they have at least a bubble. Well. I have even seen people running with nop more than a hairline of life left. Of course. That luck doesnt go to me. I cant even run after taking 40 damage encumbered or not. <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br> My best option is blast them from far away and root them if I can. If not then blast away doing melee combat and casting between their swings.		

